# Jay's Cursor Rules — New Baseline
# Full rules live in .cursor/rules/ as MDC files.
# This file is the legacy fallback for older Cursor versions.

## Always Active
- Security rules: no hardcoded secrets, no logging PII, parameterized queries, bcrypt passwords
- Workflow: Interrogation → Docs → Plan → TDD → Code → Review → QA → Ship

## Pre-Code Sequence (Never Skip)
1. Interrogate the idea — assume nothing, ask until no gaps remain
2. Generate all 6 canonical docs (PRD, APP_FLOW, TECH_STACK, FRONTEND_GUIDELINES, BACKEND_STRUCTURE, IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN)
3. /autoplan --adversarial before any feature
4. /test-gen — write failing tests first (TDD red phase)
5. Code — make tests green, 100% coverage
6. /review --dual-model before any PR
7. /qa — real browser, real auth
8. /document-release → /progress → PR

## Source of Truth Docs
docs/PRD.md, docs/APP_FLOW.md, docs/TECH_STACK.md, docs/FRONTEND_GUIDELINES.md,
docs/BACKEND_STRUCTURE.md, docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md, CLAUDE.md, progress.txt
Code must never contradict these docs. Update the doc first, then the code.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode always — no `any`, explicit return types, `interface` over `type`
- Prefer `unknown` over `any`, narrow with type guards
- No non-null assertion `!` without a comment

## React
- Function components + hooks only — no class components
- Server Components: no client-only imports. Client Components: `'use client'` at top
- No prop drilling >2 levels — use context or state library
- Controlled inputs, co-located tests, one component per file

## API
- Validate all inputs with zod at the boundary
- Consistent error shape: `{ error: string, code: string, details?: unknown }`
- Auth runs before business logic — never inline

## Database
- Every Prisma write in try-catch, transactions for multi-table writes
- Reversible migrations, no raw SQL without parameterization, add indexes for WHERE/JOIN columns

## Testing (TDD)
- Write failing test first, then minimum code to pass, then refactor
- 100% coverage on business logic — Vitest for unit, Playwright for E2E
- Test names: `it('should <behavior> when <condition>')`

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase | Hooks: usePrefix camelCase | Utils: camelCase
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | DB: snake_case | Routes: kebab-case
- Branches: feat/ fix/ chore/ prefix

## Commits (Atomic)
- One logical change per commit
- Format: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `test:`, `docs:`
- Never `git add .` — stage specific files

## Anti-Patterns (Never)
- Skip interrogation and jump to code
- Edit code without updating canonical docs
- `any` types, hardcoded secrets, `console.log` in production
- Comment out code instead of deleting, merge without passing tests

## Skills Reference
- gstack: skills/gstack/ — browser QA, workflow OS
- BMAD: skills/bmad/ — product shaping
- GSD: skills/gsd/ — structured execution
- Superpowers: skills/superpowers/ — parallel agents, TDD, worktrees
- All skills: see skills/README.md
- All agents: see .claude/agents/README.md
- All commands: see .claude/commands/
